habitat_description:
The range extends from extreme southwest Kansas, Oklahoma, south New Mexico and Texas well into northeast Mexico (Coahuila, Chihuahua, and Central Tamaulipas) (Bartlett and Bartlett 1999; Behler and King 1979; Conant and Collins 1998; Stebbins 2003).
Habitat includes prairies, farmland, and mesquite savanna. Breeding takes place in quiet waters of rain pools, cattle tanks, and reservoirs (Conant and Collins 1998; Stebbins 2003).
